92w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/George-RR-Martin-new-2-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/george-r-r-martin">乔治·R·R·马丁 (George RR Martin)</a>命名了他认为“电视史上”最佳结局的电视剧集。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/tv-features/heres-what-we-know-about-house-of-the-dragon-season-two-3333766">以下是我们对《龙之屋》第二季的了解</a></strong></li></ul><p>这位著名作家——最著名的是<a href="https://www.nme.com/series/game-of-thrones"><em>《权力的游戏》</em></a>世界的创造者——在他的网站上与他的粉丝分享了<a href="https://georgerrmartin.com/notablog/2023/08/29/perfect-episodes/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">博客更新</a>，解释了过去四分之一世纪他最喜欢的电视剧集。</p><p>这是在<a href="https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2023/08/best-tv-episodes" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>《名利场》</em></a>发表一篇文章后提出的，该文章将<em>《权力的游戏》的</em>某一集列为过去 25 年来它认为“完美”的 25 集之一。</p><p>该剧集是该剧第二季<em>《黑水》</em>的倒数第二集，该剧于 2012 年 5 月播出，主要围绕角色史坦尼斯·拜拉席恩 (Stannis Baratheon) 展开，他率领军队参加了一场争夺君临的战斗。</p><p> “我从未声称自己是完美的……但如果<em>《名利场》</em>的好人要这么说，我该与谁争论，”作者在他的页面上写道，并分享了完整列表的链接。</p><p> “当然，他们实际上并不是说我是完美的。 They are talking about <em>Blackwater</em> , one of the episodes I wrote for <em>GAME OF THRONES</em> ,” he added, also citing that although it is the favourite of the four episodes he wrote, season four episode <em>The Lion and the Rose</em> is a close contender. </p><figure id="attachment_3226624" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3226624" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3226624" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/sophie-turner-game-of-thrones-2000x1270-1.jpg" alt="Sophie Turner in 'Game Of Thrones'" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/sophie-turner-game-of-thrones-2000x1270-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/sophie-turner-game-of-thrones-2000x1270-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/sophie-turner-game-of-thrones-2000x1270-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/sophie-turner-game-of-thrones-2000x1270-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/sophie-turner-game-of-thrones-2000x1270-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/sophie-turner-game-of-thrones-2000x1270-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3226624" class="wp-caption-text"> Sophie Turner in &#39;Game Of Thrones&#39;. CREDIT: LANDMARK MEDIA / Alamy Stock Photo</figcaption></figure><p> He continued, going on to explain how he agrees with many of the other choices listed in the article – namely <em>The Suitcase</em> from <em>Mad Men</em> , <em>Ozymandias</em> from <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/breaking-bad"><em>Breaking Bad</em></a> and <em>The Pine Barrens</em> from <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/the-sopranos"><em>The Sopranos</em></a> .</p><p> However, elsewhere in the post he went on to reveal that his all-time favourite episode was not mentioned in the list – the season finale of <em>Six Feet Under</em> .</p><p> “If I had to pick one episode that was even more perfect than all the others on the list, though, it would have to be the final episode of <em>SIX FEET UNDER</em> ,” he wrote. “I liked that series well enough, though I cannot say I loved it as much as I loved <em>ROME</em> or <em>DEADWOOD</em> or <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/fargo"><em>FARGO</em></a> or a few other shows missing from the list.</p><p> “But that last episode was far and away the best finale in the entire history of television,” he continued. “And I cannot imagine how anyone could possibly do better.”</p><p> In the blog update, he also expressed his admiration for various episodes of <a href="https://www.nme.com/series/the-wire"><em>The Wire</em></a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/series/black-mirror"><em>Black Mirror</em></a> , as well as saying he felt “very pleased and flattered” to have one of his creations listed among the others. </p><figure id="attachment_3431601" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3431601" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3431601" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/George-r.r.-Martin.jpg" alt="George R.R. Martin" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/George-r.r.-Martin.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/George-r.r.-Martin-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/George-r.r.-Martin-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/George-r.r.-Martin-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/George-r.r.-Martin-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/George-r.r.-Martin-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3431601" class="wp-caption-text"> George RR Martin at House of Dragons premiere credit: Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> “No work of art is ever truly perfect, of course… but it is very gratifying to hear that maybe you achieved it, or at least came close,” he concluded. “There is always a next time, though… and regardless of how well (or poorly) one of my tales is received, I always want to do better the next time I sit down in front of the computer.”</p><p> Other series listed in the list included <a href="https://www.nme.com/series/friends"><em>Friends</em></a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/arrested-development"><em>Arrested Development</em></a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/series/sex-and-the-city"><em>Sex And The City</em></a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/series/the-office"><em>The Office</em></a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/series/succession"><em>Succession</em></a> .</p><p> In other George RR Martin news, earlier this year the writer confirmed that writing on the upcoming Thrones prequel series <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/game-of-thrones-george-r-r-martin-says-writing-on-prequel-series-will-stop-for-duration-of-strike-3440879"><em>A Knight of the Seven Kingdoms: The Hedge Night</em> will stop for the “duration” of the ongoing writer&#39;s strike in the US</a> .</p><p> “No one wanted this — no writer with an ounce of sense, anyway — but the producers and the studios and the networks and the streamers gave us no choice,” he wrote on his blog. “I am not in LA, so I cannot walk a picket line as I did in 1988, but I want to go on the record with my full and complete and unequivocal support of my Guild.”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/george-rr-martin-picks-best-finale-in-history-of-television-3492267">George RR Martin picks best finale “in history of television”</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
